Process Status

ps  <PID>
         -o                 : specify options 
         -A|-e              : all process
         -L,-m,-T|m         : show threads (LWP)
         -H|f               : forest/ASCII
         -u,-U|U            : select by user name
         -p|p               : select by pid

E.g: ps -pf 
     ps -up 

Note: BSD options : without dash , UNIX options with dash

PS Options
   
comm     =  simple name of executable
pid      =  process id
ppid     =  process parent id
%cpu     =  cpu utilization 
%mem     =  memory utilization
time     =  cumulative CPU time
etime    =  elapsed time since process start
rss      =  resident set size (in kiloBytes)
vsz      =  virtual memory size
cls      =  process scheduling policy
pri      =  process priority 
rtprio   =  realtime priority
ni       =  nice value
cgroup   = process CGroup name

